                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5727/61.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 129.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 8th instant, respecting the application to other countries of
                    the administrative changes in United States customs-houses, which derive from
                    the new German-American commercial agreement.</p>
                <p>While expressing my best thanks for this communication, I beg to inform you that
                    I immediately acquainted His Majesty’s Government with its contents.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
